%I A397788 #10 Jul 10 2026 20:18:56
%S A397788 0,0,1,1,2,0,3,1,2,0,5,0,6,0,1,2,8,0,9,1,2,0,11,1,8,0,6,2,14,0,15,4,4,
%T A397788 0,7,2,18,0,5,3,20,0,21,4,6,0,23,2,18,0,7,5,26,0,13,5,8,0,29,2,30,0,
%U A397788 10,8,16,0,33,7,10,0,35,4,36,0,8,8,22,0,39,6,18,0,41,3,22
%N A397788 Number of odd primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n.
%H A397788 Jianing Song, <a href="/A397788/b397788.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397788 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dirichlet_character">Dirichlet character</a>.
%F A397788 Let b(n) = A007431(n) be the number of primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n.
%F A397788 - If b(n) is even (i.e., n == 2 (mod 4) or n is divisible by 8 or an odd prime squared), then a(n) = b(n)/2;
%F A397788 - If b(n) is odd (i.e., n is an odd squarefree number or 4 times an odd squarefree number), then a(n) = (b(n) - (-1)^omega(n))/2.
%F A397788 In other words, if there are an even number of primitive Dirichlet characters modulo n, then half of them are even and half of them are odd; if the number of primitive Dirichlet characters is odd, then the even (resp. odd) characters outnumber by 1 if n has an even (resp. odd) number of distinct prime factors.
%F A397788 These formula can be proved using these relations:
%F A397788 - a(2) = 0, a(4) = 1, a(2^r) = A007431(2^r)/2 = 2^(e-3) for r >= 3;
%F A397788 - For odd primes p, a(p) = (p-1)/2, a(p^r) = A007431(p^r)/2 = (p-1)^2*p^(e-2)/2 for r >= 2;
%F A397788 - a(m*n) = A397787(m)*a(n) + a(m)*A397787(n) if gcd(m,n) = 1.
%e A397788 a(2^r) = 2^(r-3) for r >= 3: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters of 1+4Z/2^rZ (a cyclic group of order 2^(e-2)), then an odd primitive character modulo 2^r is an odd extension (i.e., taking -1 at -1) of chi^e for odd e.
%e A397788 a(p) = (p+1)/2 for odd prime p: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters modulo p (a cyclic group of order p-1), then an odd primitive character modulo p is of the form chi^e for odd e.
%e A397788 a(p^r) = (p-1)^2*p^(e-2)/2 for odd prime p and r >= 2: Let chi be a generator of the group of characters modulo p^r (a cyclic group of order (p-1)*p^(e-1)), then an odd primitive character modulo p is of the form chi^e for odd e coprime to p.
%o A397788 (PARI) A397788(n) = my(f=factor(n), w=#f~, num); num=prod(i=1, w, if(f[i, 2]==1, f[i, 1]-2, ((f[i, 1]-1)^2)*(f[i, 1]^(f[i, 2]-2))))); if(num%2==0, num/2, (num-(-1)^w)/2) \\ after _Antti Karttunen_'s program for A007431
%Y A397788 Cf. A007431 (number of all primitive characters), A397787 (number of even primitive characters), A359591 (excess of even primitive characters over odd ones).
%K A397788 nonn,easy,new
%O A397788 1,5
%A A397788 _Jianing Song_, Jul 09 2026
